        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 9 at 2:53AM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 252 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Edgefield County Airport, or 8 miles northeast of Belvedere, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aiken, North Augusta, Belvedere, USC Aiken, Aiken Municipal Airport,
Citizens Park, Edgefield County Airport, Graniteville, Gloverville,
Trenton, Hopeland Gardens, Murphys Estates, Vaucluse, and Murphy
Village.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 5 and 33.
Interstate 520 in South Carolina near mile marker 23.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
